import React, { Component } from "react"; class TechnicalStuff extends Component { render() { return (

// the technical stuff ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

{"<"} div id =' experience ' {">"}

{"<"} p class =' coursework ' {">"}

includes Algorithmic Game Theory, Computer Architecture, Operating Systems, Data Structures and Algorithms, Scalable and Cloud Computing, Databases and Information Systems, Software Design, Discrete Mathematics, Number Theory, as well as Automata, Computability, and Complexity.

{" p {">"}

{"<"} p class =' technicalSkills ' {">"}

comfortable w/ Java, HTML, Node.js, C, LaTeX, SQL, Git, Agile Development (Scrum), Linux/OSX, Amazon EMR, QA, and automated testing. beginner @ Python, OCaml, React, MongoDB, Android, and C++.

{" p {">"}

{"<"} p class =' professionalExperience ' {">"}

this past summer I was a software development intern at Ellucian. I spent this time working directly inbetween the devs and the QA team to optimize the automated testing suite and workflow.

{" p {">"}

{"<"} p class =' interests ' {">"}

the projects that have given me the most joy have involved full-stack development. my interests currently lie in algorithm design, game theory, software optimization, and humanitarian software development. namely, one of the things I am most passionate about is making computer science both more accessible and more approachable.

{" p {">"}

{"<"} p class =' aLifeChangingExperience ' {">"}

my current outlook on life/engineering has been largely shaped by my time in Rwanda this past summer. I taught CS at the Gashora Girls Academy of Science and Technology and helped students with a their personal projects. my favorite was using a Raspberry Pi to automate a hydroponic tomato garden (it's very difficult to get tomatoes to grow in Rwanda). my time at the academy left me with an understanding of the impact computer science can have on the lives of others. now, at the start of my professional career, I'm eager to design software that leaves a positive impact on the world and on those around me.
